   "source": [
    "We will split this into two different datasets, one for the independent features X, and one for the dependent variable y (which is the `tip` column).\n",
    "\n",
    "We’ll now split the dataset x into two separate sets `x_train` and `x_test`.\n",
    "\n",
    "Similarly, we’ll split the dataset y into two sets as well `y_train` and `y_test`.\n",
    "\n",
    "Doing this using the sklearn library is very simple. Let’s look at the code:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
